# MCU Memory Budget

Track firmware memory usage against MCU budget constraints.

## Budget Table

| Resource | Total | Warning | Critical |
|----------|-------|---------|----------|
| Flash (.text + .rodata) | 192 KB (app area) | 80% | 90% |
| SRAM_L (.data + .bss) | 32 KB | 80% | 90% |
| SRAM_U (memory_pool) | 32 KB | 80% | 90% |
| Stack | {{stack_size_kb}} KB | 75% | 85% |

## Workflow

1. **Locate ELF**: Find `output/*.elf`, fail if not found
2. **Run arm-none-eabi-size -A**: Get section sizes
3. **Parse linker script**: Get memory region definitions
4. **Calculate usage**: Compare sections vs regions
5. **Growth detection**: Compare with previous build (git)
6. **Large symbol check**: Flag symbols >1KB RAM or >4KB Flash
7. **Report**: Generate budget status with percentage bars

## Output Format

```
## Memory Budget Report

### Status: OK | WARNING | CRITICAL

| Region | Used | Total | Usage | Bar | Status |
|--------|------|-------|-------|-----|--------|
| Flash  | 150KB | {{app_flash_kb}}KB | 78% | [████████░░] | OK |
| RAM    | 22KB  | 32KB  | 69% | [███████░░░] | OK |
| Stack  | 1.1KB | 1.5KB | 73% | [███████░░░] | OK |

### Growth Since Last Commit
| Section | Previous | Current | Delta |
```
